<br>
Slow *is* powerful. You can't even do PoP zones effectively without it. But if you think it is OVERPOWERING, do we nerf it too? KEI helps with the downtime, something players begged for. As for Bristlebane, remember, I died 3 times during that fight and so did the mages (at least once each). For me, half the fight I didn't even have KEI as slow was my priority and I couldn't muster up 900 extra mana to burn before the next slow needed to be be cast. I do have a weapon I got in Hate that has unlimited charges of the 29th level Clarity. I used that on me and the mages who died till I felt comfortable enough to cast KEI. So you can only blame my overpowerd KEI on *half* the fight. <br>
<br>
So now slow and KEI is overpowering, what's next... haste? I guess I don't understand why people want the nerf bat swung so many times. You take all the things away that sets the classes apart is it even fun to play EQ anymore?<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
I don't see every enchanter doing the AA every 20 minutes thing or solo'ing Woushi or taking out named in BoT. I see a very small handful of them doing a few amazing things. Just as I see a few elite mages doing some neat things too. As Izelin pointed out, your average enchanter won't be able to do these things.<br>
<br>
/ignore those who use name-calling in a debate.<br>
