has almost no regen.  Its not COD that wins the fight, its not COD that makes this doable, its a combination of zone layout(portals next to a named, etc) and spells available that make the right combination allowing a chanter to make this happen, or in my eyes, abuse it.<br>
<br>
Every class that feels it deserves or should be master in damage dealing are the ones complaining, but FACT is chanters have been capable of outdamaging mage pets through charm or DC for at least over a year, definitely since Luclin.   If you try and take away chanters charming ability, it would be like taking away nukes from wizards or pets from mages, its what chanters do.  Chanters who maintain and keep a charmed pet do so at a great mana cost and great risk to themselves and their groups when charm breaks.  Its a tool that comes with risk.  <br>
<br>
Keep in mind since POP released chanters have been given powerful spells and tools all geared towards their ability to charm.  We have Arcane rune(1500HP shield), Eldritch Rune(1500 instant shield), new Runes and Uproar(450HP shield), total domination 3(reduces chance for charm to break), plus all the defense abilities.  Do you think Verant provided us with these because we get aggro from Tash? No, its because their plan was for chanters to use charm abilities MORE in pop then in the past.  Part of the problem is with POP chanters now have larger mana pools, can take over 3000HP in damage without losing any actual HP, allowing them to not only charm a pet, but to hold onto it almost indefinitely.  <br>
<br>
Charm isnt going away, and I hope VI recognizes that COD is a good tool for chanters and its not what needs fixing.  Just like they did with Wuoshi and making the other mobs in the zone uncharmeable, they need to look at the zones where charm is being used and eliminate the ability of a few chanters to exploit those zones.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andurravenblade>Andur Ravenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 5:04:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> I feel 1 aa point in 20 minutes is exploiting a broken ability and most people who play EQ will more then likely agree.<br>
