<br>
Soloing = Fine.<br>
<br>
How would you solo in PoP as an Enchanter without charm?<br>
<br>
If you take away an Enchanters ability to Solo here, then please be prepared to give up the same thing yourself.<br>
<br>
This mindless begging for a nerf will bring you no friends, nor will it win your cause.<br>
<br>
The reason Verant hasn't taken away CoD or just outright nerfed it is because it would take away 50% of the power that Enchanters have been given in PoP. Would you like to give up 50% of your spells? Maybe we can make it so mobs regen at 5x their normal rate unless a real tank is hitting it, that way Mages aren't putting real tanks out of a job.<br>
<br>
After all, someone mentioned that the reason CoD should be nerfed is because it will make it so nobody else can get a group. Well &quot;Pet Centered Groups&quot; are putting tanks out of a job and that's just as wrong in my opinion. Maybe Mages should only be able to summon a pet every 10-20 minutes so they aren't able to be used to replace tanks.<br>
<br>
If you say &quot;But we can't solo without them&quot; or &quot;Tanks have no trouble getting groups and the pet centered group isn't putting them out of a job.&quot;... well the same holds true for Charm groups. I don't see anyone having that much trouble getting groups so it's a moot point.<br>
<br>
Yeah I know.. I sound like an angry extremist. Which is also what many of you sound like.<br>
<br>
Again, I'd like to commend the people that have put honest forethought into their posts and offer viable alternatives.<br>
<br>
I'd like to say to those people that say &quot;Unless you can prove the risk, I just want it nerfed.&quot; Please offer something in the way of an alternative yourself instead of asking everyone else to do the work.<br>
<br>
Perhaps they will &quot;Tune&quot; some zones and mobs to balance it in tomorrow's patch. That would fix the &quot;End game encounter&quot; issues. But 20 minutes for an AA point isn't broken by any means. Especially if it involves another 30 minutes of rebuffing and meditating to get back to getting exp.<br>
<br>
Stuff like this sure brings out the ugliest in people. I hope we can get past this soon.<br>
<br>
*Edit*<br>
P.S.<br>
I killed in Plane of Growth with my Cleric/Necro combo and a level 60 Mage friend before PoP. With Alternating Rains he was parsing 250dps and could hold that for an entire fight. (Without being summoned and killed btw.) (His mana pool allowed him to do that for the duration of a 32k mob kill.)<br>
<br>
His rains were something like 3 waves of 600+ at the time. With PoP his rains are 3 waves of 900+... that would be around 350dps correct? None of that includes pet damage. Should this be nerfed too? According to some of you, the answer would be a definite yes.<br>
